{# 
    Media Source (<source>)
    ===========================================================================

    Defines multiple media resources for media elements, such as <video> and <audio>.

    Variables:
    - `source_src`: The URL of the media file. Defaults to "media-file.ext".
    - `source_type`: The MIME type of the media resource. Defaults to "video/mp4".
    - `source_media`: Specifies the media query for which the resource is designed. Defaults to "".

    Notes:
    - The `| e` filter is used to escape any special characters in the variables to prevent XSS attacks.
    - Typically used within <video> or <audio> elements to provide different formats of the same media.

    Links:
    - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/source
    - https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_source.asp

#}

<source 
    src="{{ source_src | default('media-file.ext') | e }}" 
    type="{{ source_type | default('video/mp4') | e }}" 
    media="{{ source_media | default('') | e }}"
>
